text: To those who say it is too soon to talk about gun safety reform, I say it is far past time to talk. The most impt job of members of Congress is to protect the American people, we are failing. It's time to act. #GunReformNow
I am currently writing a new bill that will restore the Obama-era mental health background check that Pres Trump repealed.

We need to keep guns out of the hands of those who have no business firing a weapon. My Handgun Trigger Safety Act promotes the development of new “smart gun” tech that only allows an authorized user to fire a gun & requires all handguns use this tech within 10 yrs.

If you need insurance to drive a car, why not require it for gun ownership? My Firearm Risk Protection Act will encourage responsible gun ownership by requiring gun owners to purchase liability insurance, which will help to ensure they use and store their guns responsibly.

I've also authored HR1832 to reverse the Dickey Amendment and allow the @CDCgov to finally study gun violence.  Gun violence is a national epidemic and we need to study its root causes so we can come up with realistic, workable solutions.

Currently, ppl buying guns at gun shows arent subject to background checks, even though 97% of Americans support universal background checks. My HR1612 will close the loophole & make sure all gun purchasers received same background check as those already in place at gun stores.

For yrs, law enforcement has asked Congress for better tools to go after gun traffickers & people who buy guns for those who are prohibited from buying guns on their own. My HR1475 Gun Trafficking Prevention Act will do just that.

What will it take for @GOP to finally say #EnoughIsEnough? For years I have been fighting for #gunsafety bills - including 5 that I wrote and I'm currently working on a 6th. @SpeakerRyan needs to listen to the American people who are shouting #GunReformNow and let us vote.

There is no such thing as a good government shutdown. @realDonaldTrump should be ashamed. #TrumpShutdown https://t.co/uJxmpJQ0FW

What about air traffic?
   
Air traffic control and the @TSA continue to receive funding during the shutdown. These essential services are not affected.

How does this effect #SmallBiz?
   
The @SBAgov stops operating its core lending & investment programs during a shutdown, meaning no new applications for loans will be granted.

Will our veterans continue to get the services they've earned and deserve?
   
All @DeptVetAffairs medical facilities and clinics will operate as usual, however, call centers and hotlines will be off. Additionally, @VAVetBenefits public contact services are unavailable.

Will we still get our mail?
   
Yes. The @USPS  is self-funded so the 500K employees are not included in the shutdown.

What about the military? Will they get paid?
   
@DeptofDefense said yesterday that all active duty military personnel will report for duty during the shutdown. According to the @washingtonpost, their pay will not be interrupted as long as the #TrumpShutdown ends before Feb 1.

How does this effect Social Security and SSI checks?
   
While during a shutdown no new social security cards are issued, all social security recipients will continue to get their benefits.
